consider me

257
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:24,767
as your best friend, Felma.

258
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:28,033
I am your best friend
and your lover.

259
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,400
I'm very sorry.

260
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,200
I feel so ashamed.

261
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:41,667
Felma, you shouldn't be ashamed
in front of me.

262
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,700
We need to be comfortable
with each other.

263
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:50,833
With the things we say,
and the things we do,

264
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:52,700
because we're about
to get married.

265
00:17:05,067 --> 00:17:06,433
But don't worry so much
about that.

266
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:11,200
You should get some rest.

267
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,233
I have a meeting to catch.

268
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:18,533
Hello?

269
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:22,933
I'm on my way there.

270
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,133
Bye.

271
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:32,833
I'll get going.

272
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,333
Thank you.

273
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,133
Be safe.

274
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:16,267
After several weeks....

275
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:18,000
Mom, why here?

276
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:22,133
What? We need to be practical.

277
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:24,167
So?

278
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:26,267
Do you want him
in our room upstairs?

279
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,733
Can you carry your dad
up and down on your own?

280
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,867
Think before you complain, okay?

281
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:41,733
Why? Are you giving me
the attitude?

282
00:18:42,367 --> 00:18:43,867
Do you want him
in the living room?

283
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,133
So everyone can see him.

284
00:18:45,267 --> 00:18:46,200
Is that what you want?

285
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:48,333
No. It's better here.

286
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:51,500
It's good because it's near
the bathroom.

287
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:54,600
Unpack his bag.

288
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:55,733
I still have to cook.

289
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:57,900
But make it fast
because I need your help.

290
00:18:58,300 --> 00:18:59,200
From now on,

291
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,900
it's just the two of us
who'll do all the work.

292
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:07,200
Oh, Dad, you're sweaty.

293
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,700
Would you like
to change clothes?

294
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:10,933
No need. No need, dear.

295
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:18,400
I'm sorry if you and your mom
are having a hard time.

296
00:19:20,067 --> 00:19:20,700
Especially you.

297
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:21,967
You still have to go to school.

298
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:23,967
Of course...

299
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:26,767
I'll be a burden to you.

300
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,767
Dad, don't think about that.

301
00:19:31,067 --> 00:19:32,900
You'll never be a burden to me.

302
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:36,367
I really don't mind
taking care of you, Dad.

303
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:39,033
We're a family, right?

304
00:19:39,167 --> 00:19:41,000
And remember,

305
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:42,567
ever since I was a baby,

306
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:44,233
you took good care of me.

307
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:47,467
Now, it's my turn
to take care of you.

308
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:55,000
Maybe I really can't match
the way you take care of me.

309
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:58,600
Dad...

310
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,633
don't think
of negative thoughts.

311
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:06,100
Everything will be okay
because we have each other.

312
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:07,033
Okay?

313
00:20:09,633 --> 00:20:10,500
Please don't cry.

314
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,500
Thank you so much, dear.

315
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:17,533
I'm so lucky to have you
as my daughter.

316
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:21,333
- I love you, Dad.
- I love you, dear.

317
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:27,900
But you know what? I'm luckier
to have you as my dad.

318
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:42,467
Here, Dad.

319
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:44,633
Do you need anything else?

320
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:51,167
Do you want to watch
on ViewTube? Or play games?

321
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,600
Or Friendsbook?

322
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,700
No, no, dear.

323
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:55,967
Thank you.

324
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,733
Go on. I can manage.

325
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:01,033
You might still have homework
to finish.

326
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:02,967
Go on, I can manage on my own.

327
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,300
No, I'm free.

328
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,067
My schedule for today
is pretty open.

329
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:08,833
Really?

330
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:13,133
Can you please hand me my phone?

331
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:14,433
Sure.

332
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:16,733
Dad.

333
00:21:16,867 --> 00:21:17,800
Thank you.

334
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:19,267
Eat your food, okay?

335
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,933
I will, thank you, dear.

336
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:28,533
Oh, Dad?

337
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,733
I hope you don't mind me asking.

338
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:37,800
But are you planning
to tell your original family

339
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:39,533
about your situation?

340
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:43,667
At least let them know
what happened to you.

341
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:45,767
Oh, dear.

342
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:47,600
I think I shouldn't do that.

343
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,000
Maybe...

344
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,300
they don't need to know.

345
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:55,733
Oh, Dad, they also have
the right to know.

346
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:57,400
Are you sure?

347
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:03,467
No. I think it's better if
I don't talk to them.

348
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:07,000
They might worry about
my situation.

349
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,233
It's better
if they don't know anything.

350
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:13,467
I don't want them to pity me.

351
00:22:14,067 --> 00:22:17,967
It'll hurt if I find out
they don't care about me.

352
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:24,700
Dad, that's not true.

353
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,200
Someone's worried about you.

354
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:31,967
What? Who?

355
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,067
- Oh!
- Dear?

356
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:40,433
I know you can't lie.

357
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:45,067
No, Dad,
I forgot I have homework.

358
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,300
See that?

359
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:47,600
You're caught.

360
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:49,067
You're lying.

361
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,767
Oh, Dad.

362
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:02,533
Miss Felma and I do keep
in touch.

363
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:07,167
How?

364
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:09,733
It's complicated.

365
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:13,500
But I'm sure Miss Felma
cares about you.

366
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:16,400
Would you...

367
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:18,000
like us to call Miss Felma?

368
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,133
We can call her.

369
00:23:25,433 --> 00:23:26,133
Do you want?

370
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:37,567
Thank you.

371
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:42,467
We've had time to date.

372
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:46,133
Are you still upset?

373
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:50,067
There are just so many questions
in my mind right now.

374
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:52,633
Go ahead, ask me.

375
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:54,900
I'll answer you.

376
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,700
What did you feel when...

377
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:04,800
you found out
your husband's condition?

378
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:08,400
Of course, I felt bad for him.

379
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:11,633
He's still the father
of my children.

380
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:15,633
Is it just pity?

381
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:19,067
Didn't you get worried
or scared that...

382
00:24:20,633 --> 00:24:23,400
he might leave this world
without forgiving him?

383
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:26,033
And the kids, too.

384
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:33,100
I prayed for him and his family.

385
00:24:34,133 --> 00:24:42,100
I prayed that we could finally
forgive him and his family.

386
00:24:42,833 --> 00:24:46,400
I don't need to see him
to forgive him.

387
00:24:48,100 --> 00:24:49,400
Will you contact him again?

388
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:52,533
I respect you and...

389
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,933
our engagement
is matters to me.

390
00:24:56,633 --> 00:25:03,900
I know you'll get hurt
if I keep checking up on him.

391
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:05,500
So, no.

392
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:09,000
It's better to keep things quiet
just like before.

393
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:13,667
Felma...

394
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:15,067
can you really do that?

395
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:19,000
Won't you worry for him?

396
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:24,267
For you
and for our relationship, no.

397
00:25:24,933 --> 00:25:25,867
Promise.

398
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:28,533
I won't call him again,

399
00:25:28,667 --> 00:25:32,700
and I won't receive any calls
from them again.

400
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:03,767
What's wrong with you?

401
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:05,667
Why did you poop there?

402
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:09,133
I'm sorry. I didn't make it
to the bathroom in time.

403
00:26:09,533 --> 00:26:11,633
I think we need to give
each other some space.

404
00:26:11,867 --> 00:26:13,600
Are you breaking up with me?

405
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:15,267
Are you calling off the wedding?

406
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,167
Is that what you want?

407
00:26:17,533 --> 00:26:19,700
Do you really want
to marry Uncle Noah?

408
00:26:20,167 --> 00:26:22,167
Or are you going
to let your relationship end

409
00:26:22,433 --> 00:26:24,800
just because you can't let go
of your ex-husband?

410
00:26:24,933 --> 00:26:27,067
I can't take care of him
anymore.

411
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:29,100
I need to take him
to a nursing home.

412
00:26:29,233 --> 00:26:30,833
What? No way!

413
00:26:30,967 --> 00:26:31,967
I'm not okay with that!

414
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:34,567
Well, I'm not asking
for your permission.

415
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,133
I'm just letting you know.

416
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,133
Dad.

417
00:26:37,267 --> 00:26:39,000
<i> Hi, Dad!</i>

418
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,033
<i> Dad, how are you?</i>
